The Gnus development sources can be accessed via CVS pserver. To use
this, you must have cvs 1.8 or newer installed.

The proper incantation for checking out the Gnus sources the first time is
this:

    $ cvs -d :pserver:gnus@cvs.gnus.org:/usr/local/cvsroot login
    CVS password: gnus
    $ cvs -d :pserver:gnus@cvs.gnus.org:/usr/local/cvsroot checkout gnus

If you just want to browse the sources, visit http://quimby.gnus.org/cgi-bin/cvsweb.cgi/gnus/

To make and install using [http://www.gnu.org/software/stow/ stow]:

<pre>
./configure
make
make install prefix=/usr/local/stow/gnus
cd /usr/local/stow
stow gnus
</pre>

----
Debian users can have a look at GnusCvsForDebian to get a Debian package of daily snapshot of Gnus.

----
